<p>
A <strong>K2 Airways Boeing 737-400 cargo aircraft</strong> carrying
<strong>five crew members</strong> has reportedly gone missing after
losing contact with air traffic control while flying from
<strong>Sharjah, United Arab Emirates</strong> to
<strong>Karachi, Pakistan</strong>.
</p>

<h2>Navigation System Failure Reported</h2>

<p>
According to preliminary reports, the aircraft informed air traffic
controllers that it was experiencing a navigation system malfunction.
Shortly afterward, communication with the aircraft was lost and radar
contact disappeared.
</p>

<h2>Search and Rescue Operation Underway</h2>

<p>
Pakistani authorities have launched an extensive Search and Rescue (SAR)
operation involving multiple agencies. Rescue teams are searching the
last known location of the aircraft as officials work to determine what
happened.
</p>

<h2>Investigation Continues</h2>

<p>
Authorities have not confirmed whether the aircraft crashed or made an
emergency landing. The cause of the disappearance remains unknown, and
aviation investigators are expected to examine all available radar,
communication, and flight data.
</p>

